Detailed Description

Class for reading native files.

A utility class used for accessing and reading data from the native file format.

DzError DzInFile::readPointer (  ) 

This method should be called to tell the parser to read a pointer from the file. If the pointer has already been fully read from file (and is not just a stored pointer reference), then setPointer() will be called on the object. If the actual object data that the pointer contains is yet to be read from the file, then setPointer() will be called at some later time prior to finishing the file load operation.

Returns:
DZ_NO_ERROR on success, otherwise an error code.
DzError DzInFile::readRot ( DzQuat &  rot  ) 

Read a rotation. This method actually reads a reduced-resolution representation, but since the quat values are all in the [0,1] range and we renormalize when we read the rotation back in, this should work fine

Parameters:
rot This will be set to the value read from the file.
Returns:
DZ_NO_ERROR on success, otherwise an error code.
